tp:treatment-sec.p:
MALE ABDOMEN. Ninth abdominal tergite slightly protruded backwards. Tenth abdominal tergite extended backwards, posterior area divided into 2 lateral lobes, apices broadened, posterior area fused with epiproct, after which is a rectangular concavity. Cercus cylindrical, lightly incurved, base slightly stout, apex tooth- shaped. Genitalia sclerotized, dorsal branch narrow, near middle leaf-shaped expanded, lateral margins of apical half parallel, apex bispinose; ventral branch stout with apex thin (
Fig. 4D
). Subgenital plate with basal half broad, apical half narrow, lateral margins parallel, apex with a pair of spine-shaped processes, moderately upcurved. Styli long, inserted near base of middle lobe.
